		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014"></a><br><code>sle2014/paper01</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>ProMoBox: A Framework for Generating Domain-Specific Property Languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/BartMeyers.html">Bart Meyers</a>, <a href="../profile/RomualdDeshayes.html">Romuald Deshayes</a>, <a href="../profile/LeviLúcio.html">Levi Lúcio</a>, <a href="../profile/EugeneSyriani.html">Eugene Syriani</a>, <a href="../profile/HansVangheluwe.html">Hans Vangheluwe</a>, <a href="../profile/ManuelWimmer.html">Manuel Wimmer</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_1">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_1</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> The paper centers on model checking of domain models via domain-specific property specification and verification.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> It generates domain-specific property languages so domain experts can state temporal properties in familiar terms.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It provides a framework that integrates property modeling and result visualization into DSM environments.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It relies on automated translation to verification back-ends (e.g., mappings to existing model checkers).
</li></ul></li></ul>
